Louis H. PINK, etc., v. Arthur C. PARSONS, etc. No. 8084. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Sept. 21, 1936. William Scallon and W. T. Pigott, both of Helena, Mont., for appellant. John G. Brown and William A. Brown, both of Helena, Mont., and W. F. O’Leary, of Great Falls, Mont, for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and mandate issued forthwith.
